cs.PL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE 

The paper presents a technique for automating data completion tasks using programming-by-example (PBE) and a domain-specific language (DSL) that combines spatial and relational reasoning over tabular data. This involves synthesizing a program to automate the desired data completion task given a formula sketch and a few input-output examples for each hole. The paper also proposes a new version space learning algorithm that is based on finite tree automata (FTA). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) due to the focus on PBE, DSL, and synthesis algorithms. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) due to the evaluation of the proposed approach on benchmarks taken from online help forums.
